        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:42AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1241 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Waldo, or near Talladega, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Waldo, Sycamore, Winterboro, Alpine, Chandler Springs,
Ironaton, and Gunthertown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
